#note I missed a nice chance here by not seeing RAMOSE or RIMOSE for 40! Failing that I think this is a reasonable play - MIS suggests he has at least another S and strong tiles to go with, and I noticed that AEIOST played unusually well on this board - TOASTIER/TOASTIES/IODATES/ISOLATE/ATONIES. I really did not want to make it easier for him to bingo, and I also saw that the vowel was very consonant-heavy. still, taking the points is clearly right.
>Moses_Peter: DLY 5J .DLY +16 356
>JD: AEIOSTU I6 .U. +10 351
#note his last play suggests a heavy leave. playing the U here helps more of my bingos go down, but also helps Peter's too by creating an S hook. At the time, I wish I'd played RUM and then tried to keep fishing for the same stuff I'd been going for (D, L, N, Rx2, Sx2 or ?, 8/12). However, on further analysis, he can often block both of my lanes with a play through the G hooking VOIDS. Really, I need to draw a bingo as soon as possible before he blocks, and PUT gives me a 10/12 chance of bingoing next turn. the worry is that my bingo will let him bingo out, but I most likely have to bingo and hope he is too consonant-heavy to respond. interesting position.
>Moses_Peter: GLNRS D11 ..NGS +10 366
